name: Ricard Lalander
text:
So, if someone had said two years ago that I would sit and review a mass vaccination site in a trade fair during a global pandemic, then I would have asked the person concerned to drink something cold and lie down for a while. But now we are here!
Werlabs in Kistamässan was a well-oiled machine. No queue on arrival, quickly inside the exhibition hall. There was hand sanitizer and mouth protection for those who needed it. Markings on the floor so you could keep your distance. Quick and friendly staff showed me to the right place and after a short wait I sat in one of the many booths that stood in a long line. It was health fair meets vaccine bus meets airport. Quick check and quick poke and then out and wait in some kind of Kafka-esque giant hall where everyone sat spread out on small plastic chairs and stared at a small digital clock, as if it would make time go faster - the quarter of an hour you have to wait for possible side effects before you can go. There was about a 50 m queue when I went home, but the day before it must have been upwards of 300 m, but the queue moved quickly. Don't come too early, because that's when there will be a queue!
All in all, a well-functioning and efficient device. Easy to get to from most parts of Stockholm and easy to find. Recommended.
topics_array: mass vaccination site, global pandemic, Werlabs, Kistamässan, exhibition hall, hand sanitizer, mouth protection, distance, quick and friendly staff, booths, health fair, vaccine bus, airport, Kafka-esque giant hall, side effects, queue, well-functioning and efficient device, Stockholm, recommended

name: Tottis Crossler
text:
Was there for vaccination.
I got there about 30 minutes before my appointment because I wasn't sure how easy it would be to find from the shuttle etc. so I got there extra early just to be safe, I couldn't stress. I expected to wait outside or walk around waiting to get in line first when it was my turn, but there was no line at all and everyone who thought like me and waited spread out outside was waved in and allowed inside right away, so I clearly chose the right time. I was vaccinated and ready (including the 15 minute extra wait afterwards) before my appointment had even passed. I was pleasantly surprised.
The staff were knowledgeable and very nice, the roller coaster was like a well-oiled machine!
There is hand sanitizer, mouth protection and clear information everywhere, as well as clear staff everywhere, so everything was very easy.
Terribly organized and flexible when it comes to vaccination anyway, they know their stuff!!! 💜
topics_array: vaccination, appointment, waiting, line, staff, knowledgeable, hand sanitizer, mouth protection, information, organized, flexible
